  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>This is a minor release with some fixes and enhancements, primarily to the new global search feature.</p><h3 id=\"id-1.8.1-TicketSearches\">Ticket Searches</h3><p>In an effort to keep search results focused, we were excluding closed tickets from many\u00a0searches, unless explicitly included\u00a0in the ticket status filter. We have relaxed this condition considerably. Any time a search keyword is present and\u00a0no statuses are explicitly filtered, closed tickets will show on\u00a0the results page.</p><h3 id=\"id-1.8.1-SearchOptimizations\">Search Optimizations</h3><p>We optimized the ticket search considerably. Particularly where it comes to searching for numbers (phone numbers, ticket numbers, etc), RepairQ\u00a0would sometimes not return results in an acceptable amount of time.</p><h3 id=\"id-1.8.1-CustomerSearch\">Customer Search</h3><p>There were some customer search persistence issues. If you had an active customer search it would override\u00a0any search keywords used in the global customer search box.\u00a0This issue has been resolved.</p>",
